  "verdict": {
    "decision": "GO",
    "crossover": "Standard observational/score-based methods collapse on the confounder+regime trap (pc/fci/gies keep the hidden-confounded pair as causal in 7.3-10.0 of 12 worlds; skeleton-SHD 3.2-4.5) while the reference interventional-CI grader holds (confounded-kept 0.33, skeleton-SHD 1.31, directed F1 0.91). The 'defeats the standard toolbox' claim holds across the set, not just coffee.",
    "difficulty_vs_error": "WEAK / honest negative: name-guessability difficulty does not predict discovery error (baseline corr 0.05-0.11). Discovery hardness comes from the structural confounder+regime trap present across the set, which the current difficulty metric (prior-F1 on names) does not capture. v0.4: push name-difficulty up AND add a structural-difficulty axis.",
    "ges": "GES errored on all worlds (causal-learn GES is numpy-2 incompatible); reported, not hidden."
  }
